8","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cutting","name":"cutting","key":"cutting","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Doug Cutting","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Elsewhere in Hadoop we have avoided the use of /tmp, since it is error-prone (it may not exist, it may not be large, etc.).  What's the justification for using it here?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cutting","name":"cutting","key":"cutting","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Doug Cutting","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2008-09-05T20:09:21.602+0000","updated":"2008-09-05T20:09:21.602+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12403777/comment/12628845","id":"12628845","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=athusoo","name":"athusoo","key":"athusoo","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ashish Thusoo","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"We have actually not hard coded this in the code. The scratch directory that the hive client side code uses is stored in the hive-default.xml and the hive-default.xml file contains /tmp/hive-${user.name} as the value of the \nhive.exec.scratchdir property.\n\nThis is completely modeled on how hadoop defines hadoop.tmp.dir in the hadoop-default.xml.\n\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=athusoo","name":"athusoo","key":"athusoo","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ashish Thusoo","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2008-09-06T07:14:52.651+0000","updated":"2008-09-06T07:14:52.651+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12403777/comment/12631075","id":"12631075","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cwhipkey","name":"cwhipkey","key":"cwhipkey","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Chad Whipkey","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"I think that rather than creating it, it would be fine to just print a nice error message if the directory does not exist.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cwhipkey","name":"cwhipkey","key":"cwhipkey","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small